						               													<description>Ancient Pub Battles is a Military Strategy Game where you can fight the battles from the 2nd Punic Wars virtually anywhere.  It pits Rome vs Carthage.  Scipio Africanus vs Hannibal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played with blocks marking infantry and cavalry on an open field with no terrain. Movement is measured with distance marker sticks, and combat is resolved with a simple dice pool mechanism.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games last for up to 8 turns, and movement order is determined through a chit pull mechanism. When a general&amp;rsquo;s chit is pulled, he may command armies in range or contact. Players may defer or jump in the turn order by rolling against a command rating for their generals on the field.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players may choose from four included historical scenarios, or build armies with a point system which also determines the winner of a battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
